HEADWORD: Orthospermous
<hw>Or`tho*sper"mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ortho-</ets> + Gr. <?/ seed.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having the seeds straight, as in the fruits of some umbelliferous
plants; -- opposed to <contr>coelospermous</contr>.</def>
<rj><au>Darwin.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

